{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyP1lYBxbEOiKrWgXcVNbOkv"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["EXERCISE NUMBER 1:\n"],"metadata":{"id":"7EEmEhnmjxZ1"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Mathematical Constants in Python's Math Module\n","\n","The math module in Python provides several useful mathematical constants, including:\n","\n","math.pi: The ratio of a circle's circumference to its diameter.\n","math.e: The base of the natural logarithm.\n","Exponential Functions\n","\n","math.exp(x): Returns the exponential of x, which is e raised to the power of x (i.e., e^x).\n","math.pow(x, y): Returns x raised to the power of y, equivalent to the ** operator in Python (e.g., 2 ** 3 equals 8).\n","Calculating Logarithms\n","\n","math.log(x, base): Calculates the logarithm of x with a specified base. If base is not provided, it defaults to the natural logarithm (base e).\n","math.log10(x): Calculates the logarithm of x with a base of 10.\n","math.log(x) or math.log(x, math.e): Calculates the natural logarithm (base e) of x."],"metadata":{"id":"TLlAEhHHcmn_"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["EXECISE NUMBER 2:"],"metadata":{"id":"pneRGesHiBhd"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import custom_math\n","\n","print(\"The value of pi is:\", custom_math.PI)\n","print(\"The value of e is:\", custom_math.E)\n","\n","print(\"The square of 5 is:\", custom_math.square(5))\n","print(\"The cube of 3 is:\", custom_math.cube(3))\n","\n","print(\"The area of a circle with radius 4 is:\", custom_math.area_of_circle(4))\n","print(\"The circumference of a circle with radius 3 is:\", custom_math.circumference_of_circle(3))\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"6qujQJRfiB92"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from google.colab import drive\n","drive.mount('/content/drive')"],"metadata":{"id":"qzQl7Bdwr2j8"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Constants\n","PI = 3.14159\n","E = 2.71828\n","\n","# Functions\n","\n","def square(x):\n","    \"\"\"Calculate the square of a number.\"\"\"\n","    return x * x\n","\n","def cube(x):\n","    \"\"\"Calculate the cube of a number.\"\"\"\n","    return x * x * x\n","\n","def area_of_circle(radius):\n","    \"\"\"Calculate the area of a circle given its radius.\"\"\"\n","    return PI * square(radius)\n","\n","def circumference_of_circle(radius):\n","    \"\"\"Calculate the circumference of a circle given its radius.\"\"\"\n","    return 2 * PI * radius\n"],"metadata":{"id":"nOKo77XsptOX"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}